{"title":"Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 119: Tom Pidcock talks 2025 focus, Olympic ups and downs, descending, and Link My Ride","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tom-pidcock-podcast","date":1732800579000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tom-pidcock-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 119: Tom Pidcock talks 2025 focus, Olympic ups and downs, descending, and Link My Ride</a></p>\n\n<p>This week on the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/cyclist-magazine-podcast\" target=\"_blank\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast</a> Will is joined by two-time Olympic gold medallist and World Champion in three different disciplines Tom Pidcock after a turbulent season that included highs at Amstel Gold Race and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/olympics-tom-pidcock\" target=\"_blank\">Paris 2024</a> as well as very public lows after <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-news-il-lombardia\" target=\"_blank\">falling out with Ineos Grenadiers management</a> in October.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Will sat down with Pidcock in November to talk about his rapid rise to power and his rapid descending skills as well as what’s on his agenda for 2025: full road focus or more mountain bike side quests?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pidcock also discusses how the media – and Netflix – portrays him, his ‘down year’ and how things could’ve gone differently, plus his self-imposed pressure at the Olympics.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally he also speaks about Link My Ride, the business that he co-founded, which aims to help cyclists around the world organise group rides. Find out more about Link My Ride and download the app <a href=\"https://linkmyride.com/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Interview begins at 8:42.</p>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Listen to <a href=\"https://shows.acast.com/cyclist-magazine-podcast/episodes/119-tom-pidcock-interview\" target=\"_blank\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 119 now on Acast</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Check out <a href=\"https://shows.acast.com/618e52740da782001471efbe/episodes\" target=\"_blank\">all episodes</a></strong></li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Also available wherever you get your podcasts</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Did you know Cyclist is also stunning monthly print magazine? Subscribe now at <a href=\"http://store.cyclist.co.uk/cycpod\" target=\"_blank\">store.cyclist.co.uk/cycpod</a> and get every issue for less than in the shops, delivered straight to your door.</em></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/joanna-rowsell-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 118: Joanna Rowsell, double Olympic gold track superstar</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/fabian-cancellara-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast episode 117: Fabian Cancellara: Classics king, Tudor Pro Cycling owner, patron of the peloton</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tadej-pogacar-interview\">Tadej Pogačar interview: Light is the crown</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                  